citations:
    citation-acok-bran-vii:
        source: source-acok
        properties:
            locator: "Bran VII"
            text_from_source: "The ashes fell like a soft grey snow. He padded over dry needles and brown leaves, to the edge of the wood where the pines grew thin. Beyond the open fields he could see the great piles of man-rock stark against the swirling flames."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Final chapter of ACOK. Bran wargs Summer and sees Winterfell burning. The party (Bran, Rickon, Hodor, Osha, Meera Reed, Jojen Reed) emerges from hiding in the crypts to find Winterfell sacked and burned. The flayed man badge of the Dreadfort is found on corpses — confirming Ramsay Snow's forces did the burning, not the ironborn. Maester Luwin is found dying in the godswood under the heart tree. He counsels Osha to separate the boys. He is mercy-killed by Osha. The party splits: Osha takes Rickon east toward the kingsroad; Meera and Jojen take Bran north. Last line: 'It was not dead, just broken. Like me, he thought. I'm not dead either.'"
